AGENTIC_LIB

NORMALISED EXTRACT

Purpose
This repository is an agentic template that runs autonomous workflows using the agentic-lib toolkit and the GitHub Copilot SDK. It converts a human-written MISSION.md into an automated pipeline that creates issues, writes code, runs tests, and opens pull requests under a supervisor agent.

High-value implementation points (actionable)
- Required GitHub secrets (exact names and permissions):
  - COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN: fine-grained PAT, GitHub Copilot -> Read permission only. Used to authenticate Copilot SDK for agentic tasks.
  - WORKFLOW_TOKEN: classic PAT with workflow scope. Required because GITHUB_TOKEN cannot modify .github/workflows/ files; used by init.yml to update workflows.
- Repository Settings (exact UI locations and required values):
  - Settings → Actions → General → Allow all actions (must be enabled)
  - Settings → Actions → General → Workflow permissions: Read and write
  - Settings → Actions → General → Allow GitHub Actions to create pull requests: Checked
  - Settings → General → Features → GitHub Discussions: Enabled (for discussions bot)
- Entry point and runtime: src/lib/main.js is the CLI entry point and exports main(args). Node engine requirement: node >= 24.0.0
- Scripts and commands (exact):
  - npm run build  -> echo "Nothing to build"
  - npm test       -> vitest --run tests/unit/*.test.js
  - npm run test:unit -> vitest --run --coverage tests/unit/*.test.js
  - npm run start  -> node src/lib/main.js
- Init command for updating agentic infrastructure: npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init
- Supervisor pipeline (literal flow): MISSION.md → [supervisor] → dispatch workflows → Issue → Code → Test → PR → Merge
- agentic-lib.toml configuration keys and effects (exact keys and allowed values seen):
  - [schedule].supervisor = off | weekly | daily | hourly | continuous
  - [paths]: mission, source, tests, features, library, docs, examples, readme, dependencies, contributing, library-sources (each maps to a relative path string)
  - [execution]: build, test, start (string commands run by workflows)
  - [limits]: feature-issues (integer), maintenance-issues (integer), attempts-per-branch (integer), attempts-per-issue (integer), features-limit (integer), library-limit (integer)
  - [tuning]: profile (min | recommended | max), model (gpt-5-mini | claude-sonnet-4 | gpt-4.1), infinite-sessions (boolean), optional knobs: reasoning-effort (low|medium|high|none), features-scan, source-scan, source-content, issues-scan, document-summary, discussion-comments
  - [bot].log-file = string path
- Testing guardrail: tests/unit includes a vitest test ensuring main() terminates without error by calling main() with process.argv set to ["node","src/lib/main.js"]

