DETAILED CONTENT

1. Getting started and prerequisites
- Write mission: create or edit MISSION.md at repository root with the human project goal in plain English.
- Ensure required secrets are added under Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions.
- Run the init command to install/update agentic infra: npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init
- Ensure Node runtime on CI/runner is Node >= 24.0.0 to match package.json "engines" field.

2. Required repository configuration and secrets
- COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN: create a fine-grained Personal Access Token scoped to GitHub Copilot with Read permission; put it in repository secrets under that exact name.
- WORKFLOW_TOKEN: create a classic PAT with the workflow scope and add as repository secret WORKFLOW_TOKEN; this token is required to programmatically modify .github/workflows/ from init.yml because GITHUB_TOKEN cannot do so.
- Actions permissions: set workflow permissions to "Read and write" and allow Actions to create pull requests; set "Allow all actions" to permit composite/use of actions used by agentic workflows.
- Enable GitHub Discussions for the repository (used by discussion bot integration).

3. agentic-lib.toml configuration reference (keys, types, allowed values, and effects)
- [schedule].supervisor: string; values: "off", "weekly", "daily", "hourly", "continuous"; effect: controls supervisor run cadence that dispatches workflows.
- [paths]: string mappings; typical values:
  - mission = "MISSION.md"
  - source = "src/lib/"
  - tests = "tests/unit/"
  - features = "features/"
  - library = "library/"
  - docs = "docs/"
  - examples = "examples/"
  - readme = "README.md"
  - dependencies = "package.json"
  - contributing = "CONTRIBUTING.md"
  - library-sources = "SOURCES.md"
  Effect: path resolution used by supervisor and agent workflows to gather repo context.
- [execution]: build/test/start commands are executed by workflows; set them to match local scripts. Example: test = "npm test".
- [limits]: numeric caps for agent behavior: feature-issues, maintenance-issues, attempts-per-branch, attempts-per-issue, features-limit, library-limit. These throttle the autonomous agents to avoid runaway changes.
- [tuning]:
  - profile: "min" | "recommended" | "max" — sets multiple internal defaults.
  - model: allowed values observed: "gpt-5-mini", "claude-sonnet-4", "gpt-4.1" — selects LM used by agents and affects cost/performance.
  - infinite-sessions: boolean — if true, sessions persist across compactions.
  - reasoning-effort: optional: "low" | "medium" | "high" | "none" — affects how much compute/time to spend on reasoning tasks.
  - other optional integer knobs: features-scan, source-scan, source-content, issues-scan, document-summary, discussion-comments — tune how many items are included into context.
- [bot].log-file: relative path for agent log output.

4. Workflow lifecycle and behavior
- Literal flow executed by the system:
  - MISSION.md is read by the supervisor agent
  - Supervisor dispatches workflows to create issues and features
  - Worker workflows use Copilot SDK to propose code changes
  - Tests are run (npm test) to validate changes
  - If tests pass, PRs are opened; merge depends on repository protections and policies
- init.yml runs daily by default and updates agentic infra; can be run manually with the npx init command.

5. CLI and scripts (commands and effects)
- npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init: updates agentic workflows in .github and seeds infrastructure; requires WORKFLOW_TOKEN for workflow file updates.
- npm test: runs vitest unit tests; use in CI status checks.
- npm run start: runs node src/lib/main.js which exports a main(args) function. main(args) prints arguments when used as a CLI.

6. Best practices and recommended protections
- For production, enable branch protection on main: require PR reviews and status checks (enable the test workflow as a required check).
- Use fine-grained tokens for COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN and minimize scopes.
- Use WORKFLOW_TOKEN only for init operations; rotate and limit its usage where possible.
- Limit agent concurrency via agentic-lib.toml [limits] to prevent excessive PR churn.

7. Troubleshooting steps (step-by-step)
- If init fails with permissions to modify .github/workflows/: confirm WORKFLOW_TOKEN exists and has workflow scope; confirm repository Actions permission to allow workflow file updates.
- If Copilot SDK authentication fails: verify COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN is a fine-grained PAT with Copilot read permission and is present in repo secrets.
- If workflows are not creating PRs: confirm Actions permission "Allow GitHub Actions to create pull requests" is checked and workflow run logs show no permission-denied errors.
- If tests fail in CI but pass locally: check Node version in CI runner; ensure Node >= 24.0.0 and that dependencies are installed in CI environment.

